Description: Would like Effective Access Auditing for DELL Powerstore shares
File System auditing in NEA hasn't been functional in sometime

split from ticket 00431849
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Joshua Sexton, Josh Olsen

What We've Learned Updated: Need to spin up a new ticket for FSAA scans on NAS

-this was not set up yet

-In this meeting we did create a host list for the one NAS device and start the FSAA collection scan

-the scan was pointing at an old host list dull of servers that don't exist

Next Steps Updated: meet with client to check on FSAA scan results
run some reports if scan was successful

Zoom meeting

send reminder email at 9:07AM

Client joined at 9:10AM

 

plan for meeting:

configure FSAA scans in NEA targeting Dell NAS

 

scan still running

66hrs = 31% = ~280M objects so far

scan set to full depth

5 probable owners

 

going to schedule another meeting next week

hopefully after the scan completes

Zoom meeting

Plan for meeting: check on FSAA scan

-run reports if it finished

 

previous scan was aborted on 03/21/25 in the after noon

-hours after we had our meeting

 

it started again on 03/30/25 but still running

-41%

 

looking through logs, it was aborted due to an abort request

 

client thinks one of their update contractors might have rebooted the server

going to let it run

 

adjusted scan depth to 2 (from full) and dropped probable owners to 3 (from 5)

set bulk import to upload incomplete scans

 

client will check it over next couple days
Invitation updated. Attendees: Joshua Sexton, Ian Ranstrom, Josh Olsen
Invitation updated. Attendees: Joshua Sexton, Ian Ranstrom

zoom meeting

 

scan completed after 12 days

bulk import completed after 4 hours

 

confirmed the AIC shows valid permissions data for shares

searching for specific groups shows folder permissions as expected

effective access returns good data

 

client is happy

 

They are running 11.5

asked about updating

 

They want to upgrade but don't expect to be able to move forward with an upgrade for more than 2 weeks.

they will open a ticket when they have a better idea as to when they can upgrade

 

answered some other questions:

NAA console access by other users requires those users have access to the SQ database

the option to export data from tables in a report requires enabling the option in the report element

-demonstrated this with the empty group report

 

client good to close other ticket as well: 00431849
Next Steps Updated: close this ticket
